ad to a striking new poem in English, Heights of Macchu Picchu, printed along with the original Spanish. This genesis of a verse translation also includes little-known biographical data, hitherto untranslated poems and prose from the years 1920 to 1945, and new translations of key poems from Neruda's Residence on Earth and Spain in My Heart.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z97831107042110 cprintz978080471079440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362127540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503621275423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503621275/original  a978-3-11-070421-1  Stanford University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles